config COREDUMP
    bool "Coredump subsystem"
    default n
    help
      Enable the VibeRTOS coredump subsystem.
      On a fault (HardFault, MemManage, BusFault, UsageFault, assert, or
      stack overflow) the CPU state is captured and stored in a .noinit
      RAM region that survives a warm reset.
      After reboot, call vibe_coredump_dump() or run the "coredump" shell
      command to inspect the saved state.

config COREDUMP_STACK_SIZE
    int "Stack snapshot size in bytes"
    default 128
    range 32 512
    depends on COREDUMP
    help
      Number of stack bytes captured near the fault point and stored
      in the coredump record.  Larger values give more context but
      consume more .noinit RAM.

config COREDUMP_SHELL
    bool "Register 'coredump' shell command"
    default y
    depends on COREDUMP && SHELL
    help
      Register the built-in "coredump" and "coredump clear" shell
      commands so the stored coredump can be inspected interactively.
